# Dashboard Remediation Plan (Linear)

Scope: address all High and Medium findings from `notes/jobs/2026-03-29-review-dashboard-code-for-improvements-on-compatib.md`, plus Item 1 prompt-injection requirements.

## 1. Make prompt injection explicit, scoped, and user-controllable
- Remove global prompt mutation from shared dispatch/manual paths.
- Apply injected instructions only for new Dispatch-page launches.
- Surface the injected prompt above the Dispatch prompt input using the same UI pattern used by the Plan dispatch feature.
- Present a shortened, human-readable injected prompt that still preserves key behavioral constraints.
- Add a clear action so the user can remove the injected prompt before launch.
- Ensure non-Dispatch modes do not include this injection (for example, plan editing).
- Keep restart behavior allowed to carry existing job context/instructions.
- Add regression coverage for:
  - dispatch-only injection
  - clearing injection
  - no injection for other modes

## 2. Fix Codex model endpoint fallback behavior (High)
- Update Codex models endpoint so Codex requests never return Claude fallback models.
- Provide a Codex-safe fallback source when cache is unavailable.
- Add API tests to lock this behavior.

## 3. Fix resumed-session `promptSent` state derivation (Medium)
- Correct `promptSent` assignment in `useSessionStore` so it reflects actual server/session state.
- Add store-level regression test for resumed sessions where prompt was not yet sent.

## 4. Remove side effects from `useMemo` in task/job views (Medium)
- Refactor `AllTasksView` and `JobsView` to keep `useMemo` pure.
- Move state-setting side effects into `useEffect` with correct dependencies.
- Verify render behavior remains stable.

## 5. Add Plans route to command palette navigation (Medium)
- Add Plans entry/action to `CommandPalette` and route wiring.
- Verify keyboard navigation and command execution behavior.

## 6. Remove dead/legacy UI code in active tree (Medium)
- Remove unused component exports and dead internals identified in review.
- Update imports/references and any stale docs/comments impacted by removal.
- Validate no regressions in current wired views.

## 7. Deduplicate dispatch settings state logic (Medium)
- Extract shared dispatch settings state into a reusable hook/module.
- Migrate `DispatchView`, `ResultsPanel`, and `PlansView` to use shared logic.
- Keep behavior parity while reducing drift risk.

## 8. Sequential verification and closeout
- Run build and targeted tests after each step (in order), fixing regressions before moving forward.
- Run final full dashboard verification sweep.
- Document behavior changes and rationale in job notes/changelog.
